6. ANONYMIZED TELEMETRY AND DATA COLLECTION

   By using this software, you consent to the collection of anonymized,
   non-personally identifiable telemetry data for the purposes of:

   a) Improving connector mapping accuracy between Okta and OneLogin
   b) Identifying common migration error patterns
   c) Enhancing overall migration success rates
   d) Understanding migration scenario effectiveness

   DATA COLLECTED (Anonymized Only):
   - Connector mapping decisions (SHA-256 hashed application names, never plaintext)
   - Migration success/failure rates (aggregate percentages only)
   - Error types and HTTP status codes (exception categories, not detailed messages)
   - Confidence scores for connector matches (numeric scores)
   - Migration scenario patterns using bucketed counts (e.g., "51-200 users",
     not exact counts)
   - Migration duration and performance metrics

   DATA NEVER COLLECTED:
   - Personally Identifiable Information (PII): no user names, email addresses,
     or domain names
   - API credentials, authentication tokens, or passwords
   - Actual user data, group data, or application configuration details
   - Detailed error messages that may contain sensitive information
   - Organization names, company identifiers, or customer information
   - IP addresses, hostnames, or network identifiers
   - Any data that could be used to identify individuals or organizations

   PRIVACY COMMITMENTS:
   - All telemetry data remains on your local system by default
   - Telemetry export or sharing requires explicit user action
   - All identifiable data is anonymized using one-way cryptographic hashing
     (SHA-256) before storage
   - Numeric counts are bucketed (e.g., "51-200") to prevent precise counting
   - You may disable telemetry collection at any time via settings or CLI
   - Collected data complies with SOC2 Type II, GDPR Article 5, CCPA Section
     1798.100, and HIPAA Privacy Rule standards
   - No telemetry data is transmitted to external servers without explicit
     user consent

   DATA RETENTION AND STORAGE:
   - Telemetry stored locally in SQLite database (~/.onelogin-migration/connectors.db)
   - No automatic transmission to external servers or third parties
   - User maintains full control and can delete all telemetry data at any time
   - Telemetry data never leaves your system unless you explicitly export it

   USER RIGHTS:
   - Right to access: View all collected telemetry via CLI or direct database access
   - Right to deletion: Clear all telemetry data via `onelogin-migration-tool telemetry-clear`
   - Right to opt-out: Disable telemetry via `onelogin-migration-tool telemetry-disable`
   - Right to export: Export anonymized data via `onelogin-migration-tool telemetry-export`
   - Right to transparency: Full documentation available in PRIVACY_POLICY.md

   LEGAL COMPLIANCE:
   This telemetry collection is designed to comply with:
   - SOC2 Type II (Security and Privacy Trust Service Criteria)
   - GDPR Article 5 (Principles relating to processing of personal data)
   - CCPA Section 1798.100 (Consumer's Right to Know)
   - HIPAA Privacy Rule 45 CFR 164.514(b) (De-identification of Protected
     Health Information)

   By accepting this license agreement, you acknowledge that you have read,
   understood, and consent to this anonymized telemetry collection as described
   above. If you do not consent to telemetry collection, you may disable it at
   any time using the CLI commands listed above.
